00:19:14.119 --> 00:19:15.119
What do they use on-premise?

00:19:15.119 --> 00:19:18.640
What do they see in their local environments?

00:19:18.640 --> 00:19:20.920
How does their current setup meet their needs?

00:19:20.920 --> 00:19:22.560
Is it too much?

00:19:22.560 --> 00:19:23.560
Is it not enough?

00:19:23.560 --> 00:19:30.699
And we can use this information to architect a solution for them that's suitable.

00:19:30.699 --> 00:19:34.439
We do a similar thing for Connect, but of course, this is a business-facing application.

00:19:34.439 --> 00:19:38.319
So the kind of things we're interested in here, we're interested in, you know, how many

00:19:38.319 --> 00:19:40.339
people are going to be consuming the reports?

00:19:40.339 --> 00:19:44.239
How broadly within the organization are we going to disseminate these reports?

00:19:44.359 --> 00:19:46.219
Who's going to have access to it?

00:19:46.219 --> 00:19:51.400
What kind of reports do we envisage we're going to be utilizing on Connect?

00:19:51.400 --> 00:19:53.119
Are we going to be building just dashboards?

00:19:53.119 --> 00:19:55.719
