00:19:55.719 --> 00:20:00.239
Are we going to use plumber APIs that different data scientists are going to hook into?

00:20:00.239 --> 00:20:05.079
So these are important considerations, and of course, we want to know, is this traffic

00:20:05.079 --> 00:20:06.599
going to be predictable?

00:20:06.599 --> 00:20:11.000
Are people based all over the globe, and for that reason, we're going to see lots of traffic

00:20:11.000 --> 00:20:12.959
at different times during the day?

00:20:12.959 --> 00:20:14.319
Or are they all based in one location?

00:20:14.319 --> 00:20:17.760
So we can anticipate that at nighttime, we're going to see a dip in traffic, and during

00:20:17.760 --> 00:20:23.959
the daytime or around certain times of the day, we're going to see high peaks in traffic.

00:20:23.959 --> 00:20:28.540
So again, these are some of the considerations that we look into when trying to figure out

00:20:28.540 --> 00:20:35.160
just what kind of RStudio Connect server setup needs to be implemented.

